blog.name: lunawings
blog.title: Moonlit wings reflect the stars...
blog.description:
~Ready Sparking!!!~ I'm "Luna" and I live in Aichi prefecture, Japan. This blog is a mix of things including stories of the events I attend, pictures of stuff I've bought, and commentary on whatever anime I'm currently watching. Some of my favorite things are: King of Prism, Love Live!, Tales of Series, Yuri!!! on Ice, Digimon, Precure, Free! I play the PriChan (formally PriPara) and Aikatsu arcade games, but my PriPara/PriChan/Pretty Rhythm (aka Pretty Series) stuff has all moved to a sideblog (see below). So please direct Pretty Series questions to my Pretty Series blog! (I'm only a casual Aikatsu fan so maybe hold back on the Aikatsu questions lol...) I'm really interested in following other bloggers in Japan, so say hi if you are!

This blog is mostly spoiler free. (I put things under a cut until a reasonable amount of time has passed.)

Pretty Series (Pretty Rhythm/PriPara/PriChan) Sideblog: pretty-idol-hell

Prism Rush Blog (translations of the King of Prism mobile game): prism-rush

Other Japan Sideblog: mdawnjpn

Friend Codes~ LLSIF(Jp): 511105977 / Prism Rush! Live: C3LU4ecE

summary: Detective Pikachu Team Shares Why They Went With Photorealistic Pokemon
title: Detective Pikachu Team Shares Why They Went With Photorealistic Pokemon
body:
Detective Pikachu Team Shares Why They Went With Photorealistic Pokemon

Credit: Warner Bros

Detective Pikachu looks like its going to be a lot of fun for Pokemon fans.

With two excellent trailers, we’ve been treated to a variety of live-action Pokemon. Now there was a lot of question on how they would be presented, the photorealistic versions have caused a stir amongst fans. They love it, hate it, or are split. Though, largely, it tends to be more in the “love it”…
